what party
you belong to, what church you
go to.

33:10.689 --> 33:15.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also, I think they have to
understand that
security of our data is a high
priority. Our

33:15.660 --> 33:20.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
systems are secure. The problem
has been that
criminals organized around the
world have

33:20.498 --> 33:25.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a vast amount of personal
information available
to them. And so they are
increasingly successful

33:25.136 --> 33:26.905 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as masquerading as taxpayers.

33:26.938 --> 33:31.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when they have gotten into
some of our
applications, it's because they
had already

33:31.776 --> 33:36.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stolen the information somewhere
else and
could in fact pretend very
effectively that

33:36.047 --> 33:37.816 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
they were the taxpayer.

33:37.849 --> 33:41.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, when members
of Congress
after the IRS, come after you
and say, why

33:41.319 --> 33:46.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
aren't you able to prevent this
kind of thing,
do you say it is just not
doable?

33:46.124 --> 33:52.063 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KOSKINEN: No, I say that we
need to and
are continuing to increase the
levels of security,

33:52.097 --> 33:57.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the authentication we require of
taxpayers
before they have access to
significant applications

33:57.202 --> 34:00.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we're developing and
continuing to roll
out.

34:00.171 --> 34:02.274 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And that's it?

34:02.307 --> 34:04.242 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOHN KOSKINEN: And that's it.

34:04.276 --> 34:09.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, and I think we have taken
down the applications
-- two applications that were
accessed by

34:09.314 --> 34:13.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
criminals masquerading as
taxpayers. And we
will bring them back up with
higher levels

34:13.718 --> 34:17.822 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of authentication. But,
unfortunately, while
it makes it more difficult, if
not possible

34:17.856 --> 34:21.192 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
