through, it will
be a little more difficult for
the taxpayers

34:21.226 --> 34:22.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to get through as well.

34:22.994 --> 34:25.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There are some
who look at
your -- well, many look at your
agency and

34:25.297 --> 34:29.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
say it feels it's been dogged by
one thing
after another. There was a
controversy a few

34:29.534 --> 34:36.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
years ago over the appearance
that the IRS
was holding up approval of
tax-exempt status

34:36.775 --> 34:39.210 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for these conservative nonprofit
groups.

34:39.244 --> 34:43.515 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was then this breach of
security. And
I will ask you in a minute about
the Panama

34:43.548 --> 34:51.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Papers. Question, is the IRS, is
it really
in a situation where it can't
win, where there's

34:51.856 --> 34:57.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
