problem after
another that is gripping this
agency?

34:57.495 --> 35:01.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KOSKINEN: Well, I think
there are always
challenges in this day and age
for agencies.

35:01.833 --> 35:07.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, ultimately, the IRS
does a remarkable
job of processing tax returns
efficiently

35:07.572 --> 35:13.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and effectively and promptly,
dealing with
taxpayers. If we have the
funding, we provide

35:13.545 --> 35:16.147 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
very good levels of service for
taxpayers.

35:16.181 --> 35:20.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we continue, like all
financial institutions,
to have challenges, as I say,
particularly

35:20.952 --> 35:24.489 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
with the organized crime
syndicates we're
dealing with all around the
world. Our systems

35:24.522 --> 35:29.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are attacked over a million
times a day by
people trying to get access,
which, fortunately,

35:29.227 --> 35:32.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
thus far, they haven't been able
to get as
far as our basic systems.

35:32.230 --> 35:37.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You mentioned
adequate funding.
It's something, I think, many
Americans look

35:37.369 --> 35:43.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
