need more money? You already
have so much.

35:43.174 --> 35:45.844 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, you know, why can't you
make do with
what you have?

35:45.877 --> 35:51.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KOSKINEN: Well, our budget
was cut for
five years in a row from 2010 to
2015 by over

35:51.049 --> 35:56.388 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
$1 billion, which meant that we
have lost
15,000 to 17,000 employees over
that time

35:56.421 --> 35:58.189 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
frame.

35:58.223 --> 36:01.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, while we need to be more
efficient and
are working to do that, at some
point -- we

36:01.092 --> 36:05.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have 10 million more taxpayers
than we had
-- at some point, you actually
begin to destroy

36:05.130 --> 36:09.634 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the effectiveness of the agency.
So whether
it's taxpayer service, taxpayer
enforcement,

36:09.667 --> 36:15.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or even protection of the
database, as we
continue to struggle for
funding, we continue

36:15.240 --> 36:16.574 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to be at risk.

36:16.608 --> 36:18.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And what does
that mean for
the American people?

36:18.810 --> 36:22.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KOSKINEN: Well, it means
that we estimate
we are collecting $4 billion or
$5 billion

36:22.080 --> 36:27.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a year less than we would if we
had 5,000
revenue agents, officers and
criminal investigators

36:27.152 --> 36:29.120 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we used to have five years ago.

36:29.154 --> 36:33.258 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It means that, as we
demonstrated this year
-- Congress gave us additional
funding for

36:33.291 --> 36:38.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
2016 for taxpayer service, and
the level of
taxpayer service on the phones
doubled. Instead

36:38.463 --> 36:44.402 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of only 37 percent getting
through, over 70
percent got through. It's a
direct line of,

36:44.436 --> 36:48.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
