one-postcard-sized filing

37:01.019 --> 37:04.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
form for every American or
virtually every
American.

37:04.289 --> 37:06.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Could something like that be an
answer for
the IRS?

37:06.624 --> 37:10.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KOSKINEN: Well, clearly,
life would be
simpler for taxpayers and
simpler for us if

37:10.261 --> 37:15.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the tax code were simpler. It
doesn't -- not
even necessarily to a postcard,
but it is

37:15.333 --> 37:18.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
obviously overly complicated for
everyone
at this point in time.

37:18.636 --> 37:24.209 align:left position:12.5%,start line:66.67% size:87.5%
So, we have been great
supporters of tax
simplification.
The policy issues are the domain
of the Congress

37:24.242 --> 37:29.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the administration. We do
tax administration,
but I have made it clear that
tax administration

37:29.114 --> 37:33.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
would be a lot easier and more
effective and
efficient if the code were
simpler. And so

37:33.585 --> 37:35.520 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
whatever we can do to support
that, we're
happy to do.

37:35.553 --> 37:39.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let me ask you
finally, John
Koskinen, about the Panama
